== Description == <!--T:2-->

</translate>
{{Codeextralink|https://raw.githubusercontent.com/2cv001/SpreadsheetDependencyInspector.FCMacro/main/SpreadsheetDependencyInspector.FCMacro}}
<translate>

<!--T:3-->
'''WORK IN PROGRESS Many changes and additions are coming.'''

<!--T:4-->
The macro '''Spreadsheet Dependency Inspector''' displays, for a selection of spreadsheet cells, all dependencies between spreadsheet cells and even between a cell and object properties. Everything is shown as an expandable tree that displays the cell name, its alias, its formula, and its value. It displays recursively:
* Cells that use other cells
* Cells that are used by other cells

<!--T:5-->
The macro is multilingual, currently supporting English and French. The language used is the one you selected in your FreeCAD preferences.

</translate>
[[File:Capture d'écran 2026-05-04 135141.png]]

[[File:Capture d'écran 2026-05-04 143828.png]]
<translate>

<!--T:6-->
As a complement to this macro you may also want to check [[Macro_Sketch_Constraint_From_Spreadsheet|Macro Sketch Constraint From Spreadsheet]].

==== Examples of use ==== <!--T:7-->

<!--T:8-->
* Get an overall view of the dependencies between cells, and between cells and object properties.
* See the consequences of deleting a cell.
* Check whether a cell is unused.
* Verify and edit expressions.
* Assign aliases or labels.
* Verify and edit labels.
* Locate in the sketch a constraint that is linked to a spreadsheet cell.
* …

== Usage == <!--T:9-->

<!--T:10-->
In a SpreadSheet, select one or several cells, then run the macro. 

</translate>
[[File:Capture d'écran 2026-05-04 194745.png]]
<translate>

<!--T:11-->
The '''refresh button''' image recalculates the analysis, for example after you modify a cell or change the selection. 

<!--T:12-->
The '''expand/collapse button''' lets you expand or collapse the whole tree. You can also do it branch by branch by clicking on the ▶ or ▼ symbols.

<!--T:13-->
Choose the information you want to display:

</translate>
